Patients will get access to ‘transformative’ treatment for HIV prevention from September on the basis of the Supreme Court’s decision to finance the NHS drug.
The National Health Service (NSH) announced that the pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP), which is taken before sex and reduces the risk of infection in high-risk patients by up to 86 percent, will be offered through health services to approximately 10,000 patients within a three-year trial period.
