The White House recruitment cost taxpayers thousands of dollars
The White House's decision to fly the Navy's helicopter to South Lawn on the occasion of the celebration of the U.S. manufacturing industry, which took place last month, came to $24,000, according to the Navy's records, published by the weekly newspaper TIME.
The green-white Sikorsky VH-3D helicopter, also called the Marine One in the presence of the president on board, was the peak of the program of July 17 in the White House, which was a show of American construction programs.
