“We were interested in whether it was a Hatch Act breach and we were assured that everything was okay,” the commander wrote.
“It sounds like you’re blocked,” the commander’s representative wrote.
This “Made in America” show was marked by the White House as an official event and the Hatch Act would not apply to it.
But even official events have political subtext.
During his participation in the events, the president promoted the health reform, which passed through the Senate, and talked about an effort to keep the government’s regulations on the ground.
Using aircraft such as Marine One or Air Force One for political purposes is hardly a new phenomenon.
The presidents use them when traveling.
However, their presence purely due to presentation reasons is unusual.
Trump ordered a check in February after the presidential aircraft went back in the background at his first meeting in the framework of the campaign in Melbourne, Florida. his Twitter account is filled with complaints about the use of the presidential aircraft by his predecessors.
“The White House is pleased with the ‘Made in America’ show, which presented products from all the 50 states that Americans manufacture from American materials,” said deputy secretary Lindsay Walters.
The HMX-1 helicopter crews often train landing in Washington and South Lawn and train possible arrivals with the President of the United States to the White House with maximum accuracy.
